column1: How would I rate the Trump Administration's response to COVID-19? That's easy: it has been a national tragedy. No strategy no plans no coordination and has cost hundreds thousands of American lives. #DelawareDebates

The Western Sussex County Democratic Club hosted their annual Drive-by Crabfeast today allowing us to grab crabs and register to vote! Thank you Sussex County for carrying out this wonderful event. #TeamLBR got a chance to enjoy crabs with while staying safe and socially distant
Getting ready to join @AymanM on @MSNBC to discuss our continued response to #COVID19 and @JoeBiden's plan to help America #BuildBackBetter

Because of the Affordable Care Act 20 million additional Americans gained quality affordable health care. Now more than ever we need to build on that and give uninsured Americans the opportunity to get insured under a special enrollment period for COVID-19. Enough. #TeamJoe https://t.co/Nf6sJb8fYx

#ICYMI - Yesterday Governor John Carney announced that Delaware’s Presidential Primary originally scheduled for April 28th will be postponed and rescheduled for June 2nd 2020 due to COVID-19 concerns.
